{{Infobox school | name = Gjimnazi Zenel Hajdini | logo = | image = Zenelhajdini2.jpg | alt = | caption = | motto = | motto_translation = | location = [[Gjilan]] | country = [[Kosovo]] | coordinates = {{Coord|42.468055|21.465533|display=inline,title}} | other_name = <!-- or | other_names = --> | former_name = <!-- or | former_names = --> | type = [[High School]] | established = 1945 | opened = 1945 | closed = | district = | grades = 10-12 | director = Sami Hoxha | superintendent = | principal = | staff = | faculty = | gender = Middle School, Gymnasium | age_range = | lower_age =15 and | upper_age = 19 | enrollment = <!-- or | enrolment = --> | campus_size = 1200km2 | campus_type = Campus | language = [[Albanian Language|Albanian]] | team_name = | newspaper = Gjimnazisti | colors = Blue and White | communities = | yearbook = Libri i Gjenerates | feeders = | website = <!-- {{URL|example.com}} --> | footnotes = }}
'''Gjimnazi Zenel Hajdini'''<ref name="IslamiJugoslavije1986">{{Cite book|last1=Islami|first1=Hashim|last2=Jugoslavije|first2=Savez arhivskih radnika|title=Arhivski fondovi i zbirke u arhivima i arhivskim odeljenjima u SFRJ: SAP Kosovo|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=tkRmAAAAMAAJ|accessdate=24 September 2010|year=1986|publisher=Savez arhivskih radnika Jugoslavije}}</ref> is a high school in [[Gjilan]], [[Kosovo]], and it was founded in 1945. In 1964 it took the name of People's Hero [[Zenel Hajdini]]. In 1969 the [[Turkish language]] started to be taught along [[Albanian language]] and [[Serbian language]]s. A new building hosted the school in 1973. Today the school hosts around 2,300 students.
==Organisition== [[File:Zenel hajdini.jpg|thumb|left|Students in their free lessons]] The "Zenel Hajdini" Gymnasium works under the frameworks and curriculum of the [[Ministry of Education, Science and Technology (Kosovo)|MEST]] of the [[Kosovo|Republic of Kosovo]], and it is one of the most successful gymnasiums in the Balkans Peninsula. Teaching is offered in Albanian and Turkish, with Albanian being the main teaching language. It is one of the most competitive high schools in Kosovo, with annual applications far exceeding the available spots.
