{{about|the Slovenian magazine|other uses|Joker (disambiguation)}}
{{Refimprove|date=September 2014}}
[[image:JokerMagazineLogo.jpg|thumb|right|200px|''Joker'']]
'''''Joker''''' is a [[Slovenia]]n monthly [[magazine]]. Started as a [[Computer and video games|computer gaming]] magazine, it has expanded into reviewing books, movies, educational articles of a general nature and much more. Known for having an interesting writing style which also includes [[archaism|archaic]] and [[neologism|neologistic]] [[Slovene language|Slovene]] words.

''Joker'' was founded in May 1992 under the wing of ''[[Moj mikro]]''. The first edition was [[duotone]] and because of poor sales it was cancelled. In September 1993 it was revived as a [[a5 paper size|half-sized]] addition to ''Moj Mikro''. In January 1994 it had grown into an independent magazine of full size format. A [[compact disc]] was added in December 1995 and a website was launched in March 1996. In December 2000 ''Joker'' became the first Slovenian magazine and one of the first in the world to include a [[DVD]] with every copy. Since 2015 Joker has also a digital edition for iOS and Android.

It also has a [http://www.joker.si/ website] with an archive containing much of the content from the magazine and one of the largest Slovenian online message boards called [http://www.joker.si/mn3njalnik/ mn3njalnik]. [http://www.joker.si/mn3njalnik/index.php?showforum=17 Gnojišče] is sub forum on this board and is the Slovenian equivalent of [[4chan#.2Fb.2F|/b/]]. 

