[[Image:TRNC Passport Map.png|thumb|300px|right|
Countries and territories with visa-free entries or visas on arrival for holders of regular Turkish Cypriot passports.
{{legend|navy|Northern Cyprus}}{{legend|green|Visa free}}{{legend|red|Pre-arrival visa required}}{{legend|gray|Countries in which the passport is not valid}}
----
More details: [[Visa requirements for Northern Cypriot citizens]]]]

'''Northern Cypriot passports''' are issued to citizens of the self-declared state of [[Northern Cyprus]] (TRNC) for the purpose of international travel. The passport is valid in only a few countries in the world due to the [[Foreign relations of Northern Cyprus|limited international recognition of Northern Cyprus]]. A Northern Cypriot passport is valid in [[Anguilla]],<ref>[http://www.gov.ai/immigration/forms/Immigration_visa_requirements_anguilla_2007.pdf Anguilla Official Website] Visa Requirements for Anguilla</ref> [[Pakistan]], [[Tanzania]],<ref>[http://immigration.go.tz/module1.php?id=31 Tanzania, Official Government Website, Visa] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160304090034/http://immigration.go.tz/module1.php?id=31 |date=2016-03-04 }} Name of the Country: Northern Cyprus</ref> [[Turkey]], and the [[United States]].<ref>http://www.trncinfo.com/index.asp?page=272  {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100528043841/http://www.trncinfo.com/index.asp?page=272 |date=May 28, 2010 }}</ref><ref>[http://www.europarl.europa.eu/sides/getDoc.do?type=WQ&reference=E-2015-005940&format=XML&language=EN European Parliament]</ref> [[Turkish Cypriot]]s are also issues [[Turkish passport]]s.<ref name=anthro>{{Cite book| publisher = Psychology Press| isbn = 978-0-415-30409-2| last = Conference| first = Association of Social Anthropologists| title = Human Rights in Global Perspective: Anthropological Studies of Rights, Claims and Entitlements| url=https://books.google.com/books?id=bagvCwvAGVsC&pg=PA84 |date = 2003}}</ref>

Until 1994 entry to the [[United Kingdom]] was easier on an "unrecognised" TRNC passport then a Turkish passport. Many [[Kurdish people|Kurds]] and other political dissidents paid high prices to obtain TRNC passports which they used to enter the UK visa-free and claim [[political asylum|asylum]].<ref name=anthro />
