The '''Union for the Presidential Majority''' ({{lang-fr|Union pour la Majorité Présidentielle}} '''UMP''') is the ruling political coalition in [[Djibouti]]. The coalition supports the Presidency of [[Ismaïl Omar Guelleh]].<ref>http://www.ump.dj/article.php?ID=1{{dead link|date=July 2016 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref>
The coalition originally formed to contest the [[Djiboutian parliamentary election, 2003|2003 parliamentary election]], and support Guelleh in the [[Djiboutian presidential election, 2005|2005 presidential election]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.crwflags.com/fotw/flags/dj%7D.html|title=Djibouti - Political Party flags|website=www.crwflags.com|access-date=2017-09-17}}</ref>
The coalition is composed of five parties; the [[People's Rally for Progress|RPP]], the [[Front for the Restoration of Unity and Democracy|FRUD]], the [[National Democratic Party (Djibouti)|PND]], the [[Social Democratic People's Party (Djibouti)|PSD]], and the [[Union of Reform Partisans|UPR]].<ref>http://www.ump.dj/article.php?ID=5{{dead link|date=July 2016 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref>
